parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the ABS system can cause extended stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on and stays on
the vehicle jerks or vibrates when applying the brakes
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brakes make a grinding noise
the vehicle slows down but continues to glide when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause loss of braking ability, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.
